If you want to convert the time column to string, you need to use [`CAST(time AS char)`](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.5/en/cast-functions.html#function_cast) or [`CONCAT(&#39;&#39;,time)`](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33232078/) on the `CREATE_PROCEDURE` query used to create ``spdAdminGetPIREPS``


Alternatively, You can get the raw binary data using [`resultSet.getBytes()`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/sql/ResultSet.html#getBytes(int)) and change it back to ``string`` through `blob` using [`Utilities`](https://developers.google.com/apps-script/reference/utilities/utilities#newBlob(Byte)):

```
function byteArrToString(byteArr){
 return Utilities.newBlob(byteArr).getDataAsString();
}
```
